The respondent in case DIS-IHK-2025-01180 asserts that the Deutsche Institution für Schiedsgerichtsbarkeit e.V.(DIS) lacks jurisdiction to administer the dispute. The respondent bases this assertion on clause 6.2 of the Engagement Letter dated July 1, 2020. According to the respondent, clause 6.2 stipulates that all disputes arising from the agreement shall be settled under the Rules of the Munich Chamber of Commerce Rules of Arbitration by a single arbitrator. The respondent argues that there is no agreement to submit disputes to DIS, therefore DIS lacks jurisdiction.

Elcomponics Sales Pvt. Ltd. ("Respondent") submitted a response to the Request for Arbitration dated 6th May 2025 filed by FAMAS Gmbh. The Respondent raised a jurisdictional objection to the arbitration request. This response was submitted on behalf of Elcomponics Sales Pvt. Ltd. by its duly authorized Company Secretary, Anu Sharma, who is authorized to represent the company in this matter. The Respondent contends that the Request for Arbitration is inadmissible and requests that DIS decline jurisdiction over the matter.

Famas GmbH initiated arbitration proceedings against Elcomponics Sales. The arbitration is governed by the Rules of IHK Munchen. Elcomponics states that there is no provision in the Engagement Letter permitting submission of disputes to DIS or adoption of DIS procedural rules. Elcomponics claims it never consented to arbitration under DIS rules.

The Respondent, Elcomponics Sales Pvt Ltd, contends that the Request for Arbitration is inadmissible because DIS (presumably an arbitration institution) lacks jurisdiction to administer the dispute. The Respondent argues that submitting the dispute to DIS is inconsistent with the parties' agreement and represents an attempt by the Claimant to unilaterally impose a forum not agreed upon in the Engagement Letter. Consequently, the Respondent requests that DIS decline jurisdiction over the matter. The Respondent reserves the right to submit further evidence, arguments, or documentation to support this jurisdictional objection and to engage legal counsel if necessary.

Elcomponics Sales Pvt. Ltd. ('Respondent') submitted a response to the Request for Arbitration filed by F AMAS GmbH on May 6, 2025, under case reference DIS-IHK-2025-01180.
